      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can and roughly chop</p><p>Carefully squeeze <strong>roasted garlic</strong> out of the skins and mash with a fork, discard the skins</p>",
